    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-05-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <head>426. Memorandum of a Conversation, Department of State, Washington, May 19,
                        1955<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d426fn1">Source: Department of State,
                        Central Files, 721.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/5–1955. Secret.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_ARS1">Atwood</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1955-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1955</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Increased Military Grant Aid Assistance to Colombia</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_ZAE1">Eduardo
                            Zuleta</persName>-<persName>Angel</persName> of Colombia</item>
                    <item>Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_OSA1">OSA</gloss>—Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ARS1"
                            >Atwood</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Following brief introductory remarks, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHF1"
                        >Holland</persName> brought up the request made by Colombia for increased
                    grant military aid. He explained fully to the Ambassador the lengthy discussions
                    which had been held with the Department of Defense regarding Colombia’s request
                    and regarding the overall military program in this hemisphere. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName> explained that on three separate
                    occasions the conclusion had been reached that it would be impossible at this
                    time to increase military grant assistance to Colombia. He reminded the
                    Ambassador that the Defense Department considered the alliance [<hi
                        rend="italic">agreement</hi>?] made to turn over the equipment to the
                    Colombia–Korea battalion as an increase in grant aid. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName> added that of course this was not the
                    last time that military grant aid assistance to Latin America would be discussed
                    and that he did not feel that the door was completely closed and locked for the
                    future. He did feel, however, that in the light of the extremely careful
                    analyses that had been made regarding the possibility of additional aid to
                    Colombia that it would not be productive to initiate any further discussions at
                    this time. The Ambassador was visibly disappointed but seemed to recognize and
                    appreciate the situation as described by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHF1"
                        >Holland</persName>.</p>
            </div>
